Getting Started
Prerequisites

Node.js 18+
A React project setup (Vite, Create React App, etc.)

Installation
bash# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/your-username/student-results-manager.git
cd student-results-manager

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start the dev server
npm run dev
Usage

Drop the component file into your React project's src/ folder
Import and render it as the root component:

jsximport App from './student-results-manager';

function Root() {
  return <App />;
}

Open the app in your browser, upload a student result file, and click Show Results.


 Supported File Formats — Column Requirements
For best results, your file should contain at least:
ColumnAccepted Header NamesRoll Numberroll, id, reg, enroll, htno, hallticket, usn, prnStudent Namename, studentSGPA / CGPAsgpa, cgpa, gpa, cpi, cumulative, spiBacklogsbacklog,
arrear, kt, atkt, fail, supplyBranchbranch, dept, department, stream, programSectionsection, sec, div, division

PDF files: The parser uses spatial text extraction. It works best with university result PDFs that include Roll No, grade columns (with 0 for failed subjects), and SGPA in a
tabular format.
